articles.title: King Charles and Queen Camilla Receive Warm Welcome in Sydney, the First Leg of Their Two-City Australian Tour - PEOPLE
articles.description: King Charles and Queen Camilla arrived in Sydney, Australia, on Friday, Oct. 18 and were greeted with royal images projected onto the Sydney Opera House. They will head to Canberra before departing Australia for Samoa on Wednesday, Oct. 23.
articles.content:
King Charles has been to Australia 16 times previously but this visit, which is his first as monarch, is markedly different than those before it.
